  "prompt": "Has the fear of a non wanted pregnancy, as no anticonceptive method is 100% fireproof, ever hindered your desire to have sexual intercourse?",
  "response": "The fear of an unintended pregnancy is a common concern for many people, given that no contraceptive method is entirely foolproof. This fear can indeed impact someone's desire to engage in sexual intercourse. It's important for individuals to consider their comfort level with the risk, no matter how small, and to discuss contraception options and preferences with their partner. Open communication about fears, expectations, and contraceptive methods can help alleviate some of the anxiety and make the decision to engage in sexual activity more informed and consensual. If the fear significantly hinders one's desire, it might be helpful to consult with a healthcare provider to explore all available contraceptive options and find the most suitable one.",
